	<Title>
		Heat cramps from exercise?
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;Heat cramps are painful, involuntary muscle spasms that occur during heavy exercise in hot environments. You&apos;re most likely to get heat cramps in the calf, arm, abdomen and back. Next time you experience heat cramps, here&apos;s what to do: 1. Rest briefly and cool down. 2. Drink clear juice or an electrolyte-containing sports drink. 3. Gently stretch and massage the affected area. 4. Call your doctor if the cramps don&apos;t go away in an hour.&lt;/p&gt;
